args:
Menoetius approaches the despondent Chelsea
and entices her to control Luca. When she
refuses, he goes on the attack, but Luca comes
to the rescue. Afterward, the imperials strike
again, and the two of them join forces and fight
back together.
I'm a burden. A cute, adorable thorn\nin his side.
You're that dragon from the alley.
Cheer up, child. Weren't you going to\nteach me about the true nature of love?
Yeah, I'm all out of love right now.\nI'm nothing but a big fat albatross.
I can't do anything to make Luccy happy,\nbut I still make him go along with all of\nmy crazy demands.
I'm nothing but dead weight to him.
I have no right to be with him.
Ah, but what if I told you differently?\nWhat if there was a way for you to remain\nat his side, even being such a burden?
Burn. Raze. Pillage. That is how you\nwill win all that you desire.
That's just more forcing things on—
And what's wrong with a little force?\nYou want to be with him, yes?
Then the answer is simple: Bend him to\nyour will by force. Subjugate him to your\ndesires. Erase all hurdles before you.
All the love you could ever want awaits.\nSuch is your dream, is it not?\nThen you have only to make it true.
All the love I could ever want...\nTeeee hee hee hee hee hee!
Menoetius... Menoetius... Oh, of course!\nPrometheus talked about him!
Prometheus is one of four siblings,\nand Menoetius is an older brother.
I knew he had brothers, but I can't say\nI ever knew their names.
Still, he spoke quite harshly about him,\nwhich was surprising given how cool-\nheaded he usually is.
Family troubles, eh? So what's this\nMenoetius guy like?
Prometheus mentioned a long chain of\nharassment far beyond what could be\ndismissed as mere sibling rivalry.
Yes, he had the look of someone who\nwould enjoy that sort of thing. ...Hmm?\nWait a moment.
Is that why he came to us in the first\nplace? Because he knew we were friends\nof Prometheus?
You think he's trying to get at his brother\nthrough us?
A dangerous thought; the things he said\nwere more than a little threatening,\nand the one at greatest risk right now is—
Do you finally see the light? At their root,\nlove and control are one and the same.
You needn't entertain any feelings of guilt.\nGo and lay claim to that which you desire.
I don't want to control Luccy—\nI'm certain of that now.
Stubborn fool. Control IS love,\nand love is control!
In this world, strength is all! If you would\nhave your dream realized, you must bring\nthe object of your love to heel by force!
That'd just be pushing one-sided love\non him.
And yeah, I know that's all I've had this\nentire time, which is why I always feel\nso dang anxious.
But I've never once wanted to make\nLuccy love me against his will.
I won't allow anyone to threaten Luccy—\nand that includes me!
What utter rot. I think I may be ill.
To think I bent over backward to dumb\nthings down to your level by talking of\n＂love＂ and ＂romance.＂ Utter garbage.
And the stream of treacly slop gushing\nfrom between your slackened jaws is\nthe worst kind of useless.
Wait, so everything you said before was\na lie? You actually DIDN'T want to learn\nabout love?
Do you need me to draw you a diagram?\n...Ah, well. You're a disappointment,\nbut I have other options still.
Just having him know he helped to make\nthe body count in this place higher will be\nentertainment enough.
I made such a mess of things and you got\nmad and...and I thought you hated me.
I ain't the type to hate somebody over that.
Just don't go running off again, okay?
Tch. That didn't split the two of you up?
Buddy, I am done listening to a THING\nyou have to say.
Love by force is no love at all!
If we let her live, she'll interfere with\nour occupation efforts! Cut her down!
Perfect. One pile of rubbish\ncan now take out the other.
Let him go! We've gotta take care\nof these losers right now!
Yeah, you're right. You good to fight?
Yep! We'll show 'em our love\nis unbeatable!
